race.comment: Competitive. FLASHY ICON (7) deserved his big heavily-bet Maiden win on the Canberra synthetic over 1900m and resumed with a narrow defeat here over 1400m. Presents of the fresh side and Collett stays aboard. The step up to the mile suits and with average luck she can go one better. PETAWAWA (2) won a CL1 here from the front by a space over 1400m and then was outgraded at Randwick off a wide gate. Draws the rail and will be back on speed today. Rates strongly and will take plenty of pegging back. CARAVANSERAI (6) is a leader and followed a narrow defeat here over this trip with a distant second placing behind Craft at Canberra, on a slow track. Drops in grade and will give a sight. MISS DEFY (8) will strip fitter and is still shy of her best. She's well in the mix.
